quotes.quote: It's sad to know I'm done. But looking back, I've got a lot of great memories.
You got to go down a lot of wrong roads to find the right one.
Anything's possible if you've got enough nerve.
Never pick a fight with an ugly person, they've got nothing to lose.
The truth is, everyone is going to hurt you. You just got to find the ones worth suffering for.
If you're losing your soul and you know it, then you've still got a soul left to lose.
It's not enough to be nice in life. You've got to have nerve.
If you shoot for the stars and hit the moon, it's OK. But you've got to shoot for something. A lot of people don't even shoot.
If you can't appreciate what you have got then get what you appreciate.
It is no use saying, 'We are doing our best.' You have got to succeed in doing what is necessary.
Don't compromise your self, you're all you got.
A good name is seldom got by giving it oneself.
It's impossible to give it all you got and fail unless you fail to give it all you got to do the impossible.
As long as the day lasts, let’s give it all we got.
It’s easy to be independent when you’ve got money. But to be independent when you haven’t got a thing-that’s the Lord’s test.
You can’t just sit there and wait for people to give you that golden dream. You’ve got to get out there and make it happen for yourself.
We've got to live, no matter how many skies have fallen.
No one would ever have crossed the ocean if he could have gotten off the ship in a storm.
Well, if everything stays the same forever, you stop enjoying what you've got. And stop appreciating people.
If you want to make good use of your time, you've got to know what's most important and then give it all you've got.
I got you to look after me, and you got me to look after you, and that's why.
A real friend's got your back, while the fake ones are sticking knives in it.
If you do what you always did, you will get what you always got.
You've got to get up every morning with determination if you're going to go to bed with satisfaction.
If you want to do something, go for it—you’ve got nothing to lose.
